            "children": [
              {
                "text": "The First Disaster comes at the end of Act 1, roughly 25% of the way into the story. The First Disaster is something bad that forces the Protagonist to commit to the story. "
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Example – Star Wars:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "In the original Stars Wars Movie (Episode 4), Luke's aunt and uncle are murdered by stormtroopers. This drives Luke to agree to leave the planet with Obi-Wan Kenobi. He's now committed to the Rebellion, and he can't turn back."
